##CCENT 013 - Configuring SSH, User Accounts & Password Encryption

#SSH
	1. Configure Your Hostname
		-
	2. Configure a Domain Name
		-'ip domain-name <name>'
	3. Generate Encryption Keys
		-'crypto key generate rsa'
		-How many Bits in the modulus '2048'
	4. Enable SSH Version
		-'ip ssh version 2'
	5. Create Local User Account(s)
		- Global Config 'username <username> secret <password>'
	6. Choose to Allow Telnet and SSH
		-'line vty 0 15'
		-'transport input [telnet] [ssh]'
		-'login local'
